        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 12:50PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 1249 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Millbrook, or 14 miles southeast of Rhinebeck, moving southeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amenia, Kent, Sharon, Millbrook, Stanfordville, Cornwall Bridge,
Wingdale, Dover Plains, Gaylordsville, Warren, Cornwall, Smithfield,
Salt Point, South Dover, Lithgow, Skiff Mountain, Lower Merryall,
South Amenia, Shunpike, and Shekomeko.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
